B.a1_={memory_matrix:0,sudoku:1,speed_match:2,color_match:3,number_stream:4,pattern_trail:5,train_of_thought:6}
B.akh=new A.mp("A grid flashes a pattern for a few seconds \u2014 your job is to remember it and tap the same squares back.","Your hippocampus holds the image while your prefrontal cortex keeps it alive long enough to act on it.","This is basically the N-back task in disguise \u2014 the single most studied working memory exercise in neuroscience, replicated across 24 brain-imaging studies.")
B.akf=new A.mp("Place digits 1\u20139 so no number repeats in any row, column, or box. Simple rule, genuinely hard to master.","The front of your brain works overtime here \u2014 planning ahead, holding constraints in mind, and catching your own mistakes.","Brain scans taken while people solve Sudoku show clear spikes in prefrontal activity \u2014 the same region that suffers most when you're stressed or sleep-deprived.")
B.akd=new A.mp("A card appears \u2014 does it match the one before it? Tap Yes or No as fast as you can before the timer wins.","The part of your brain that detects conflict and the one that processes where things are both have to fire together, fast.","The ACTIVE trial \u2014 the longest brain-training study ever run \u2014 found that this exact type of speed training kept paying off a full decade later.")
B.akj=new A.mp("The word says RED but it's printed in blue. Tap the actual ink color \u2014 not the word. Your brain will fight you on this.","You're forcing your brain to suppress the obvious answer and pick the correct one instead \u2014 that's pure inhibitory control.","This is the Stroop task, and it's been used in research for nearly a century. It's the go-to test for attention and impulse control, especially in ADHD studies.")
B.ake=new A.mp("Equations drift down the screen and you have to solve them before they disappear. Speed and accuracy both matter.","Both sides of your prefrontal cortex light up \u2014 one for the math, one for keeping track of what's already gone.","After just 4 weeks of this kind of training, brain scans showed measurable growth in working memory and processing speed (Nouchi et al., PLOS ONE, 2013).")
B.aki=new A.mp("Dots appear one by one \u2014 watch the sequence, then tap them back in the exact same order from memory.","Spatial memory lives in the hippocampus; keeping the sequence straight pulls in your right frontal and parietal regions too.","This is a direct version of the Corsi Block test \u2014 a staple of clinical neuropsychology since the 1970s, still used today to assess memory and brain injury.")
B.akg=new A.mp("Trains are heading for stations \u2014 tap the junctions to reroute them to the right color before anything crashes.","You're constantly switching between tasks and tracking multiple things at once, which hammers your prefrontal and parietal cortex.","Managing several moving objects simultaneously is one of the clearest ways to stress-test executive attention \u2014 the skill that tends to slip first under fatigue or distraction.")
B.a_y=new A.ba(B.a1_,[B.akh,B.akf,B.akd,B.akj,B.ake,B.aki,B.akg],A.aS("ba<q,mp>"))
